Here are two of the nicest carbine mags that you will find outside of factory wrappings. 
Got these years ago new in wrap, unwrapped them and....never used them.
Have plenty of 15 rounders and probably will never own an M2, so these would be better off in the hands of a collector or an M2 owner who wants correct mags to display with the gun.

They are:

WWII Seymour Split back 30-rounders in nearly flawless condition, with a couple small exceptions. See the pics here (21 high resolution images) http://tinypic.com/a/3s9ea/2

As you can see in the second picture, there are three small yellow circles indicating tiny surface rust spots. These will probably chip off easily enough but I want the buyer to see exactly what these are. There are also numerous very VERY tiny scratches overall, but many of these are pressing/drawing scratches from when the mags were made. See near the feed lips...some bright areas where the bluing is gone....still, very tiny areas and as you look at the tops of the mags, no big insertion scrapes showing, and the followers are perfect, indicating these mags have never had a single round in either. 
I wiped all the oil off these to show all the imperfections....oil them up and most of the tiny marks won't even show, but if you own NOS mags, you probably know this.

Beautiful bluing overall, perfect floorplates, nice SEY markings for Seymour, classic split back design with nice clean spot welds, clean drain holes pinched front fold and not a single dent or ding anywhere. Aside from the marks I mentioned, these mags are in about as perfect condition as you will ever find and will make a nice pair for your collection! You won't find new mags anymore, especially in this shape as they all have dried up and the price is skyrocketing. Get these while you can!

But be sure and take a good look at all the images.....you can save then to your PC and zoom in on any details....you'll see these mags are really, REALLY NICE!
